1. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper deals with graph signal processing, which is a subfield of network analysis. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper discusses the development of robust GSP algorithms, which involves machine learning techniques. 
3. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the effects of errors in the adjacency matrix on GSP methods, which can be analyzed using information theory. 
4. cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) - The paper involves simulations to study the graph error effect on the performance of GSP methods, which can be considered as a numerical analysis problem. 
5. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper discusses the representation of data using adjacency matrices, which can be considered as a data structure problem.
